        <h2 class="headline headline--normal">Symptoms of a Herniated Disc</h2>
        <p>
          When compressed, the spinal nerves or cord do not work properly.
          Compressed nerves will pass abnormal signal into the limbs, or worst
          signals may not get sent at all. Common symptoms of a herniated disc
          include: Stabbing, Shooting, Burning Pain, Electric feeling in limb,
          Muscle Weakness and Tingling & Numbness
        </p>

